<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-428-057  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 428 057.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  August 1 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>EDS obtains Army SMC contract. (Electronic Data Services Inc.,andO;Small Multi-user Computer, US Army Information Systems Selectionand Acquisition Agency)</TITLE><AUTHOR>McMullen, Barbara E.; McMullen, John F.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Electronic Data Systems Corp. (contracts).andO;Topic:     United States. Army. Information Systems Selection and AcquisitionAgencyMilitaryGovernment ContractsComputer systems integrationInformation Systems.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>EDS OBTAINS ARMY SMC CONTRACT ALEXANDRIA, VIRGINIA, U.S.A., 1990 AUG 1 (NB)-- Electronic Data Services (EDS) has announced that it has been awarded theSmall Multi-user Computer (SMC) contract with the U.S.andP;  Army InformationSystems Selection and Acquisition Agency to provide multi-user micro-computersystems and services to the Army, the Navy, and the Defense Logistics Agency.andM;The contract, which places EDS in the role of a systems integrator utilizingproducts and services from more than 50 vendors, is an &quot;indefinitedelivery/indefinite quantity&quot; (IDIQ) contract and runs for eight years inone-year increments.andM;Under the terms of the contract the government may choose to buy between 40and 20,000 systems and, if the maximum number is purchased, the contract'svalue can reach $700 million.andM;The three agencies involved will be able to order hardware and services fromthe SMC contract during a five-year window after initial acceptance tests atFort Huachuca, Arizona.andM;Sharon O'Malley, EDS regional director of public relations, told Newsbytesthat &quot;The contract is very exciting because of its potential.andP;  In addition tothe systems integration and providing of hardware and software, we will beresponsible for training and maintenance.andP;  The heart of our systems will bePrime EXL320s running SVID multi-user systems.andP;  In addition to the multi-usercapability of the Prime systems, we will provide integration with both DOSand UNIX based personal computers.&quot;andM;(Barbara E. McMullen andamp; John F. McMullen/199000801/Press Contact: Randy Dove,EDS, 703-742-1511)</TEXT></DOC>